The paper discusses a fundamental approach to designing fault-tolerant services, which suggests that it could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new approach to parallelism in state-machine replication, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper discusses the implementation of the proposed approach, which could suggest that it belongs to the Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-category. The paper also compares the performance of the proposed approach to other proposals, which could suggest that it belongs to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the deterministic execution of commands, which could suggest that it belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
